- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the vertex coloring problem is a well-known problem in graph theory and combinatorics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes new integer linear programming formulations for the problem, which is a common technique used in AI. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper evaluates the new models using Gurobi, which is a popular optimization solver used in machine learning. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as optimization techniques are commonly used in robotics. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possibility as the vertex coloring problem is known to be NP-hard, which is a topic studied in computational complexity.
